asset.hookText:
Effective dust pick-up across floor types relies on two things: a powerful brush bar to agitate and loosen dust and dirt, and powerful suction that pulls it away. 

The newly configured brushbar on DC65 has 25% more power to dig up dirt from carpet, while 12 highly efficient cyclones spin it out and into the bin. Dyson's Head of Product Innovation, Stephen Courtney, explains how others rely on a filter to trap fine dust, whereas DC65 can use it as a second line of defense.
